.SH Description
.PP
The function \f[C]MPI_Group_incl\f[] creates a group \f[C]group_out\f[]
that consists of the n processes in \f[C]group\f[] with ranks
\f[C]rank[0]\f[], \&..., \f[C]rank[n\-1]\f[]; the process with rank i in
\f[C]group_out\f[] is the process with rank \f[C]ranks[i]\f[] in
\f[C]group\f[].
Each of the n elements of ranks must be a valid rank in \f[C]group\f[]
and all elements must be distinct, or else the program is erroneous.
If \f[C]n\f[] = 0, then \f[C]group_out\f[] is \f[C]MPI_GROUP_EMPTY\f[].
This function can, for instance, be used to reorder the elements of a
\f[C]group\f[].
.SH Note
.PP
This implementation does not currently check to ensure that there are no
duplicates in the list of ranks.
